MATCHA Dataset & Code License

Project: MATCHA: A Multi-Disease Chinese Mental Health Dataset with Cross-Lingual Analyses on Social Media Authors: Baihan Li, Bingrui Jin, Zitong Li, Kunyao Lan, Kenny Q. Zhu, and Mengyue Wu 


1. Permitted Use
This repository, including all code, annotation prompts, and sample data, is provided for Academic and Non-Commercial Research Purposes Only.

2. Restrictions

Non-Commercial: You may not use the material for commercial purposes without explicit permission from the authors.

No Redistribution of Full Data: This repository contains only de-identified sample data. The full MATCHA dataset is distributed through a controlled-access system. Users are prohibited from attempting to re-identify any individuals in the dataset.



Ethics Compliance: Users must adhere to the ethical standards described in the paper, ensuring that the data is handled with the utmost respect for user privacy and mental health sensitivity.

3. Attribution
If you use this code, the annotation prompts (e.g., the Qwen-3 screening logic), or findings from the MATCHA dataset in your research, you must cite the following paper:


Li, B., Jin, B., Li, Z., Lan, K., Zhu, K. Q., & Wu, M. (2025). MATCHA: A Chinese Multi-Disease Mental Health Dataset with Cross-Lingual Analyses on Social Media. TechRxiv.

4. Disclaimer
The contents are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. The authors are not responsible for any misuse of the research framework or data samples.
